# Beacon Point — Project Rules

## Brand
- Name: "Beacon Point" (always two words, always capitalized)
- Tagline: "Your fixed point when everything is moving."
- One-line pitch: "We take over the non-clinical coordination burden for the first 14 days home."
- NON-CLINICAL service. Never use language implying medical authority.

## Design
- Fonts: Cormorant Garamond (display) + DM Sans (body) via next/font/google
- Never use Inter, Roboto, Arial, system fonts
- Primary: evergreen #2E4639, fern #3D5A4C, sage #5B7B6A, moss #8BA89A, mist #C5D4CB, linen #EBF0ED, ivory #F7F5F0
- Accents: sand #D4B896, clay #9B6B5A, gulf #6B8FA3, shell #E8DDD0
- Background: ivory #F7F5F0 for pages
- Shadows: evergreen-tinted rgba only (not gray)
- Radius: 8px default, 12px cards, 16px hero

## Performance (Lighthouse 100 target)
- Default to server components. Only "use client" for interactivity.
- Use next/image for all images with explicit width/height
- Use next/font/google for fonts (no external stylesheet links)
- No third-party scripts on public pages
- CSS transitions only — no animation libraries
- All animations wrapped in @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)

## Motion
- Hover: 120ms ease-out
- Click: 80ms ease-in
- Reveal: 600ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)
- No bouncing, no snapping, no playful overshoot. CALM.

## Tone (for copy and placeholder text)
- Concrete over abstract. Tasks over feelings.
- Never: "journey," "empower," "holistic," "seamless," "passionate"
- CTA: "Start a conversation" not "Book now"

## Accessibility
- 4.5:1 contrast minimum
- 44px touch targets
- Visible focus rings (2px solid sage, 2px offset)
- Skip-to-content link
- One h1, then h2 for sections, h3 for sub-sections
- All images: descriptive alt text

## Code
- Tailwind with bp- prefix for brand colors
- Public components: BP prefix (BPHero, BPPricing)
- Dashboard components: Dash prefix (DashModel, DashPersona)
- Deploy: Vercel. Use Vercel Analytics + Speed Insights.
- No localStorage for auth — use middleware + cookies

